{"analytics_identifier":"OT506","base_path":"/government/organisations/government-equalities-office","content_id":"3df55660-43a9-4494-8146-a0a492a975b6","description":"The Government Equalities Office leads work on policy relating to women, sexual orientation and transgender equality. We are responsible for a range of equalities legislation.","details":{"acronym":"GEO","alternative_format_contact_email":"accessible.formats@cabinetoffice.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Government Equalities Office leads work on policy relating to women, sexual orientation and transgender equality. We are responsible for a range of equalities legislation.</p>\n</div>","brand":"cabinet-office","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Government<br/>Equalities Office"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[{"href":"/government/organisations/government-equalities-office/about/accessible-documents-policy","title":"Accessible documents policy"}],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/minister-meets-leading-researchers-in-womens-health-and-calls-for-more-women-working-in-stem","image":{"alt_text":"Photo of Minister for Women, Maria Caulfield, speaking with members of University College London Hospital’s maternity team in a hospital corridor. All figures in the photo wear a mask.","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64073a40e90e0740d4ce8103/s712_1.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64073a40e90e0740de266a7f/s465_1.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64073a40d3bf7f56f5e075c1/1.png"},"public_updated_at":"2023-03-07T13:20:17.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Today (Monday 6 March) the Women’s and Health Minister, Maria Caulfield met leading researchers and discussed their work to improve health outcomes for women and babies, and the importance of women working in STEM (science, technology, engineering, and maths).</p>\n</div>","title":"Minister meets leading researchers in women’s health and calls for more women working in STEM"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/kemi-badenoch-asks-for-examples-of-bad-guidance-on-single-sex-spaces","image":{"alt_text":"Minister for Women and Equalities, smiling","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f85d120ab0e20c4b9c27/s712_Kemi.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f85df3e54f33b3bb08ba/s465_Kemi.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f85dd0030b10e56a50b9/Kemi.png"},"public_updated_at":"2024-05-01T09:05:59.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Minister for Women and Equalities, Kemi Badenoch MP, is calling on members of the public to send real-world examples of public bodies – and those that advise public or private bodies – that could be wrongly stating that people have a legal right to access single-sex spaces according to their self-identified gender.</p>\n</div>","title":"Kemi Badenoch asks for examples of bad guidance on single-sex spaces"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/new-report-seeks-to-end-ineffective-business-edi-practices","image":{"alt_text":"Inclusion at Work Panel report words in image","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f8d1f3e54f33b3bb08bc/s712_IAW_PN_2.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f8d1d0030b10e56a50bc/s465_IAW_PN_2.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6631f8d18f2d27f1da6a50a3/IAW_PN_2.png"},"public_updated_at":"2024-03-20T07:00:02.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The independent Inclusion at Work Panel has today published a report on the state of equality, diversity and inclusion (EDI) business practices in the UK.</p>\n</div>","title":"New report seeks to end ineffective business EDI practices"}],"ordered_featured